The paper discusses the integration of multiple viewpoints in agent-based simulations, which is a common topic in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS) and multi-agent simulations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses the temporal dynamics of multi-level simulations, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (AI) and simulation. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the influence/reaction principle, which is a common topic in the field of complex systems and system dynamics. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses implementation-oriented approaches, which is a common topic in the field of distributed computing (DC). Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category.
